{
  "buggy_files": ["drivers/acpi/video_detect.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["video_detect_dmi_table"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The Acer TravelMate 5735Z (board BA51_MV) has a non-functional ACPI video backlight brightness control when using the default acer-wmi vendor driver. The native ACPI video backlight interface works correctly. The issue is that the system is missing an entry in the video_detect_dmi_table that would force it to use the native backlight mode instead of the vendor (acer-wmi) driver. The fix requires adding a DMI entry with the video_detect_force_native callback to match this specific system and force the use of native ACPI video backlight support, which the user confirmed works (providing 15-16 brightness levels instead of 5)."
}

